<P>Mr. Alder&s;on, curate, removed to All-Saints.</P>
<P>William Lambe, A. M. rector, 1733, vicar of Che&s;ter-le-Street&mdash; died at Gate&s;head May 29th, 1769, and was buried in the choir.</P>
<P>Mr. George Steven&s;on, curate, removed to St. Andrews.</P>
<P><PB N="505" REF="542">Mr. Pool, curate, removed to Che&s;ter-le-Street, where he died.</P>
<P>Mr. Spooner, curate.</P>
<P>Mr. Wil&s;on, curate, died 8 May, 1773.</P>
<P>Mr. Bu&s;by, curate and &s;chool-ma&s;ter&mdash;removed to Hexham.</P>
<P>Andrew Wood, A. M. rector, 1769&mdash;of Baliol-College, Oxford, rec|tor of Darlington, and chaplain in ordinary to the King.&mdash;He died of a fever, Thur&s;day, 13th March, 1772, and was buried in the choir.</P>
<P>Richard Fawcett, D. D. rector&mdash;vicar of Newca&s;tle&mdash;collated, in 1772, to the rectory of Gate&s;head.</P>
<P>&mdash;Denton, curate.</P>
<P>John Falcon, A. B. curate and &s;choolma&s;ter.</P>
<P>Mr. Frederick Farren, curate and &s;urrogate&mdash;re&s;igned in 1776.</P>
<P>Mr. Farrier, curate&mdash;re&s;igned.</P>
<P>Robert Wil&s;on, A. B. re&s;igned.</P>
<P>Augu&s;t 13th, 1782, Robert Thorp, A. M. was inducted to this rec|tory, vacant by the death of Doctor Fawcett.&mdash;He re&s;igned for this promotion the vicarage of Chillingham, and the perpetual curacy of Doddington,&mdash;chaplain to the garri&s;on of Berwick upon Tweed, and afternoon lecturer of St. Ann's in Newca&s;tle upon Tyne.</P>
